description:
This course is designed to be a continuation of program and algorithm development and analysis;
search/sort methods, dynamic memory management, abstract data types and object-oriented design;
designing and debugging larger programs. Course has a required lab component. Four hours lecture/
lab per week.

Lubrication procedures; servicing air filters; servicing cooling systems; servicing hydraulic systems;
and installation, removal, and storage of batteries. One hour lecture and four hours laboratory per
week.
